6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to school athletics; declaring right
of schools to broadcast certain games; prohibiting
8 certain Oklahoma Secondary School Activities
Association contractual agreements from preventing
9 school broadcasts; stating applicability of act;
defining terms; providing for codification; providing
10 an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 27-200 of Title 70, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Schools shall have the right to broadcast all high school
19 athletic activities in this state in which the school's athletic
20 team is participating.
21 B. If the Oklahoma Secondary School Activities Association
22 enters into an exclusive broadcast agreement for an athletic
23 activity, such agreement shall not prohibit a local broadcaster or
24
